ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Within the past 12 months when I drank alcohol: 2. I felt more tired than I usually feel the next morning.
Notes: 1 = Never (0% of the time); 2 = Occasionally (about 25% of the time); 3 = About half the time (50% of the time); 4 = Most of the Time (75% of the time); 5 = Every Time I Drank Alcohol (100% of the time); -888 = NA

ElementDescription: If NEVER (0% OF THE TIME) is NOT SELECTED, in the past 12 months, how many times did you feel more tired than usual the next morning after drinking alcohol?
Notes: 1 = 2 times or less (once or twice per year); 2 = 3-11 times (less than once per month); 3 = 12-51 times (more than once per month, but not every week); 4 = 52 times or more (once per week or more frequently)
